Security has been beefed up ahead of the Nairobi International Trade Fair that will take place at Jamhuri Park from October 3 to 9.President Uhuru Kenyatta is expected to officially open the 14th edition of the show on October 7.Police officers from neighbouring counties have been deployed to the capital ahead of the event.Traffic personnel will be assigned to direct motorists heading to and from the venue.Police have asked visitors to heed instructions for the sake of order.The show will focus on value addition, agro-processing, market diversification, product launches and delivering value to stakeholders.